Use an in-memory server with two real clients. Wait for edge durability, then retry the reader query and normalize rows by stable ID:

```ts
const server = await startLocalJazzServer({ inMemory: true });
const alice = await createDb({ appId: server.appId, serverUrl: server.url, adminSecret: server.adminSecret, driver: { type: 'memory' } });
const bob = await createDb({ appId: server.appId, serverUrl: server.url, adminSecret: server.adminSecret, driver: { type: 'memory' } });
try {
  const created = await Promise.all(
    ['c', 'a', 'b'].map((title) => alice.insert(app.items, { title }).wait({ tier: 'edge' })),
  );
  const expected = new Map(created.map((row) => [row.id, row.title] as const));

  await vi.waitFor(async () => {
    const actual = (await bob.all(app.items, { tier: 'edge' }))
      .filter((row) => expected.has(row.id))
      .map((row) => [row.id, row.title] as const)
      .sort(([a], [b]) => a.localeCompare(b));
    expect(actual).toEqual([...expected.entries()].sort(([a], [b]) => a.localeCompare(b)));
  });
} finally {
  await Promise.all([alice.shutdown(), bob.shutdown()]);
  await server.stop();
}
```
Replace `app.items` and `title` with the application schema fields.

Use separate policy-test sessions and assert the different denial shapes: reads are filtered, while writes reject.

```ts
let testApp: PolicyTestApp;

beforeEach(async () => {
  testApp = await createPolicyTestApp(app, permissions, expect);
});
afterEach(async () => {
  await testApp.shutdown();
});

it('denies Bob access to Alice’s row', async () => {
  const alice = testApp.as({ user_id: 'alice', claims: {}, authMode: 'local-first' });
  const bob = testApp.as({ user_id: 'bob', claims: {}, authMode: 'local-first' });
  const row = alice.insert(app.todos, { title: 'Private' }).value;

  await expect(bob.all(app.todos.where({ id: row.id }))).resolves.toEqual([]);
  bob.expectDenied((db) => db.update(app.todos, row.id, { title: 'Denied' }));
});
```
This assumes the policy records the creator and restricts non-owners; repeat `expectDenied` for delete if deletion is also in scope.
